WEBVTT

00:12.846 --> 00:14.982
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:15.015 --> 00:16.783
ZOYA,
THEY'RE RELEASING ME.

00:16.817 --> 00:18.318
MAKE A PLAN
FOR BOTH OF US.

00:19.386 --> 00:20.153
I'M NANCY.

00:20.187 --> 00:21.688
I'M HERE AS A FREE AGENT.

00:21.722 --> 00:23.123
I WANT WEED.

00:24.758 --> 00:26.493
YOU REMIND ME
OF YOUR SISTER.

00:26.527 --> 00:29.663
YOU ARE ON PROBATION.
GOAL ONE ‐‐ EMPLOYMENT.

00:29.696 --> 00:30.797
YOU START TOMORROW.

00:30.831 --> 00:32.132
DENNY, NANCY.
NANCY, DENNY.

00:32.165 --> 00:34.501
TELL HIM
WHAT KIND OF WEED YOU WANT.

00:34.535 --> 00:35.536
OOPS.

00:36.837 --> 00:39.139
DOUG?
DANA.

00:39.173 --> 00:41.575
Wilfred: IT MUST BE HARD, DOUG,
SEEING DANA SETTLED.

00:41.608 --> 00:44.144
NAME'S DETECTIVE OUELLETTE.
25th PRECINCT.

00:44.178 --> 00:45.979
COME WORK FOR ME.
INTERNSHIP.

00:46.013 --> 00:47.047
FUCK, YEAH.

00:47.080 --> 00:48.982
I'M OPENING
A NEIGHBORHOOD BIKE SHOP

00:49.016 --> 00:50.517
THAT SELLS
THE COPENHAGEN WHEEL.

00:50.551 --> 00:52.286
THIS IS GONNA BE
A LEGITIMATE BUSINESS.

00:52.319 --> 00:53.954
THE MAIN SPACE
IS ALL YOURS.

00:53.987 --> 00:55.088
DRUG STUFF IN THE BACK.

00:55.122 --> 00:56.123
THIS ISN'T WHAT I WANTED.

00:56.156 --> 00:57.157
I NEED MESSENGERS ‐‐

00:57.191 --> 00:58.358
GOOD‐LOOKING MESSENGERS.

00:58.392 --> 01:00.827
MIDTOWN, WEST VILLAGE,
LOWER EAST SIDE.

01:00.861 --> 01:02.629
WHO'S THAT GUY?

01:02.663 --> 01:03.931
Doug:
THAT'S KLEIN, THE C. E. O,

01:03.964 --> 01:05.933
I BUILT IT
FROM THE GROUND UP.

01:05.966 --> 01:07.201
I LIKE YOU.

01:07.234 --> 01:09.603
WHAT ARE YOU?
D. E. A.? FBI?

01:09.636 --> 01:12.506
S.E.C.
THE ACCOUNTING DIVISION
AT YOUR FIRM

01:12.539 --> 01:14.041
REPORTED ILLEGAL ACTIVITY.

01:14.074 --> 01:15.676
ARE YOU SUGGESTING
A DEAL?

01:15.709 --> 01:17.911
WE NEED FILES.
PROOF, IF YOU WILL.

01:17.945 --> 01:19.346
SOMEBODY'S NO FUN TODAY.

01:21.615 --> 01:22.916
Nancy: ZOYA.

01:22.950 --> 01:24.184
HELLO, LOVER.

01:27.654 --> 01:29.656
[ HUMMING ]

01:48.242 --> 01:50.744
NOW I KNOW WHY YOU NEVER CAME
TO VISIT.

01:50.777 --> 01:52.880
[ SIGHS ]

01:52.913 --> 01:54.848
[ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

01:54.882 --> 01:56.850
SLOWER, PLEASE.
I MEAN, I GET THE GIST.

01:56.884 --> 01:57.851
I TRUSTED YOU!

01:57.885 --> 01:59.887
[ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

01:59.920 --> 02:00.921
SHUT UP, GUSENITZA!

02:00.954 --> 02:02.089
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

02:02.122 --> 02:03.924
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO,
OSLIHA? HIT ME?

02:03.957 --> 02:05.926
I'M NOT
5 YEARS OLD ANYMORE.

02:05.959 --> 02:08.462
[ SHOUTING IN RUSSIAN ]

02:08.495 --> 02:09.796
COULD WE DO ENGLISH?

02:09.830 --> 02:11.231
DID YOU JUST CALL HER
A DONKEY?

02:11.265 --> 02:13.534
GO AHEAD, ZOY.
SHOW HER THOSE EARS, HUH?

02:13.567 --> 02:15.035
[ LAUGHS ]

02:15.068 --> 02:16.904
HEE‐HAW, HEE‐HAW!

02:16.937 --> 02:18.071
T‐THAT'S NOT NICE.

02:19.640 --> 02:20.807
HOW DID YOU GET OUT?

02:20.841 --> 02:22.309
I CAN MAKE DEALS,
TOO.

02:24.311 --> 02:26.113
GO TO YOUR ROOM,
LITTLE BOY,

02:26.146 --> 02:27.414
AND TAKE YOUR SHIT
WITH YOU!

02:44.464 --> 02:48.569
HEE‐HAW!

02:50.504 --> 02:53.373
UNH!

02:54.942 --> 02:56.476
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:01.048 --> 03:02.749
[ SIGHS ]

03:02.783 --> 03:05.586
H‐HE SMELLED LIKE YOU.

03:05.619 --> 03:07.387
HE IS NOT ME.

03:07.421 --> 03:09.189
[ SNIFFS ]

03:09.223 --> 03:13.560
WHAT HAPPENED TO OUR DREAM,
NANCITCHKA?

03:13.594 --> 03:15.395
HUH?

03:15.429 --> 03:17.364
VERMONT?

03:17.397 --> 03:21.568
I‐I JUST NEEDED TO MAKE
A LITTLE MONEY...

03:21.602 --> 03:23.403
WHO DO YOU BELONG TO?

03:23.437 --> 03:26.473
[ MUMBLES ]

03:26.507 --> 03:28.942
NANCITCHKA...

03:28.976 --> 03:31.311
TELL ME.

03:31.345 --> 03:32.546
WHO?

03:34.915 --> 03:37.718
YOU.

03:37.751 --> 03:39.052
[ BREATHES HEAVILY ]

03:40.420 --> 03:44.191
GOOD ANSWER.

03:44.224 --> 03:47.160
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

03:53.834 --> 03:56.036
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]
MODERN TRANSPORTATION
FOR MODERN TIMES.

03:56.069 --> 03:57.704
TWO WHEELS GOOD.
FOUR WHEELS BAD.

03:57.738 --> 04:00.807
HEY, WANT A PICTURE OF ME
NEXT TO THE BIKE?
YEAH. YEAH, YEAH.

04:00.841 --> 04:03.076
THE BACK DOOR'S JAMMED.
THERE'S...

04:04.645 --> 04:07.281
...A PADLOCK ON IT NOW.

04:07.314 --> 04:08.215
HMM.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.917
WONDER
WHO PUT THAT THERE.

04:09.950 --> 04:11.585
KEEPING SPACES SEPARATE...
RESPECTFULLY.

04:11.618 --> 04:14.555
IT'S A WAREHOUSE BACK THERE.
IT'S INDUSTRY SECRETS.

04:14.588 --> 04:15.689
BIX MULLEN. HI.

04:15.722 --> 04:17.958
I'M DOING A STYLE SECTION PIECE
ON THE COPENHAGEN WHEEL.

04:17.991 --> 04:19.760
CAN I ASK A COUPLE QUESTIONS
JUST ABOUT THE BIKE ‐‐

04:19.793 --> 04:21.628
UH, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

04:21.662 --> 04:23.797
IT'S FOR THE BIKE, THE WHEEL.
FREE PUBLICITY.

04:23.830 --> 04:26.967
BUT WE DON'T
WANT PUBLICITY.

04:27.000 --> 04:28.168
WE DON'T ‐‐ WE DON'T WANT
MORE PEOPLE HERE.

04:28.202 --> 04:29.403
I WANT MORE PEOPLE HERE.

04:29.436 --> 04:31.371
ANDY...

04:31.405 --> 04:33.774
You're not gonna
mess up my business

04:33.807 --> 04:35.409
with your ‐‐
your silly wheel.

04:35.442 --> 04:38.712
"SILLY WHEEL," YOU SAY.
WELL...

04:38.745 --> 04:41.715
PERHAPS LESSENING OUR RELIANCE
ON FOREIGN OIL IS SILLY.

04:41.748 --> 04:43.016
HMM?

04:43.050 --> 04:45.185
WE'RE TREADING LIGHTLY
ON THE EARTH

04:45.219 --> 04:47.020
SO FUTURE GENERATIONS

04:47.054 --> 04:49.022
CAN ENJOY OUR LIMITED
NATURAL RESOURCES.

04:49.056 --> 04:52.426
[ SIGHS ]

04:52.459 --> 04:55.796
IN FACT, IF LIVING RATIONALLY
AND RESPONSIBLY

04:55.829 --> 04:58.098
ON THIS PLANET IS SILLY,

04:58.131 --> 05:00.234
CROWN ME
THE PRINCE OF SILLY,

05:00.267 --> 05:04.438
RULING CLEANLY AND KINDLY
OVER ALL OF SILLYOPOLIS.

05:04.471 --> 05:06.106
THAT LAST PART,
I'M NOT SO SURE ABOUT,

05:06.139 --> 05:07.608
BUT THE STUFF BEFORE
WAS VERY GOOD.

05:07.641 --> 05:09.343
YEAH. DO YOU THINK WE COULD GET
ONE OF HIM BY THE BIKE?

05:09.376 --> 05:11.712
YEAH. STAND NEXT TO THE BIKE,
SILAS.
NO.

05:11.745 --> 05:13.680
ONE SEC. HOLD ON.

05:13.714 --> 05:15.315
COME HERE.
I GOT A ‐‐

05:15.349 --> 05:18.685
HEY, I HAVE
A GREAT IDEA.

05:18.719 --> 05:19.987
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE A BREAK

05:20.020 --> 05:21.321
FROM THINKING ABOUT YOURSELF
ALL THE TIME

05:21.355 --> 05:22.823
AND CONTRIBUTE
TO SOMEONE ELSE'S DREAM?

05:22.856 --> 05:24.825
LIKE MINE...RIGHT NOW.

05:24.858 --> 05:27.861
SMILE FOR THE CAMERA.
COME ON. MODEL.

05:27.895 --> 05:30.898
LIVE GREEN.
SAVE THE EARTH.

05:30.931 --> 05:32.900
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]
GOOD?

05:32.933 --> 05:34.735
THANK YOU.

05:39.173 --> 05:41.808
WITH BEAUTY
COMES TEMPERAMENT.

05:41.842 --> 05:43.844
WHERE WAS I?
AH, CARBON FOOTPRINT.

05:43.877 --> 05:45.512
FEED THE WORLD. YES.
SO...

06:32.226 --> 06:35.829
POOR BABY DIDN'T GET
WHAT SHE CAME FOR, DID SHE?

06:35.863 --> 06:39.032
NO. SHE DIDN'T.

06:45.706 --> 06:47.374
[ SIGHS ]

06:48.976 --> 06:51.078
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
SHE WAS HERE?

06:51.111 --> 06:54.414
I CALLED.
IT WENT TO VOICEMAIL.

06:54.448 --> 06:56.950
YOU MUST HAVE BEEN
ON THE SUBWAY.

06:56.984 --> 06:58.719
YOU DIDN'T TELL HER ANYTHING,
DID YOU?

06:58.752 --> 07:01.088
SHE CAN'T ‐‐ AHH!

07:01.121 --> 07:02.956
SHE CAN'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT ME ‐‐

07:02.990 --> 07:05.959
WHERE I LIVE OR WORK
OR WHERE MY FAMILY IS.

07:05.993 --> 07:07.995
[ SIGHS ]

07:08.028 --> 07:09.162
I KNOW HER. SHE ‐‐

07:09.196 --> 07:13.534
Zoya: STOP IT!
GET AWAY FROM ME!

07:13.567 --> 07:14.501
[ SIGHS ]

07:14.535 --> 07:16.136
SHE TALKS IN HER SLEEP.

07:16.170 --> 07:18.238
I KNOW.
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:22.910 --> 07:25.112
AHH!

07:25.145 --> 07:26.613
AHH!

07:29.950 --> 07:33.320
LET'S MAKE THIS QUICK.

07:33.353 --> 07:35.556
AS IF.

07:38.258 --> 07:39.426
AHH.

07:49.403 --> 07:51.071
LEAVE THE DRUGS.

07:52.673 --> 07:53.941
LEAVE THEM.

07:53.974 --> 07:56.743
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY.

07:57.945 --> 08:01.148
GOOD NIGHT.

08:08.589 --> 08:09.590
BOTWIN!

08:11.792 --> 08:12.893
OH, HI.

08:12.926 --> 08:15.062
SIT DOWN.

08:18.065 --> 08:22.035
I WANT TO TELL YOU
A STORY.

08:23.504 --> 08:26.139
AT 6:30 THIS MORNING,
UPON SEEING YOUR EMPTY BED,

08:26.173 --> 08:29.343
I MADE A CALL
ARRANGING YOUR TRANSPORTATION

08:29.376 --> 08:30.210
BACK TO PRISON.

08:30.244 --> 08:32.045
AND I FELT ALL RIGHT
ABOUT IT.

08:32.079 --> 08:34.815
HAD MY COFFEE,
READ SOME FILES.

08:34.848 --> 08:38.118
AND AT 7:00,
I GOT A CALL BACK INFORMING ME

08:38.151 --> 08:40.621
THAT NOT ONLY HAD MY PETITION
BEEN DENIED,

08:40.654 --> 08:42.456
BUT THAT YOU WERE
TO BE RELEASED TODAY...

08:42.489 --> 08:46.660
FROM THIS HALFWAY HOUSE
INTO THE REAL WORLD

08:46.693 --> 08:49.930
DUE TO AN ARRANGEMENT
THEY COULD NOT SHARE.

08:49.963 --> 08:52.666
YOU KNOW,
FROM TIME TO TIME,

08:52.699 --> 08:57.337
I HAVE A CLIENT
IN WHOM I BELIEVE I SEE PROMISE.

08:59.606 --> 09:02.976
I WAS WRONG ABOUT YOU.

09:03.010 --> 09:04.611
YOU'RE A LIFER.

09:04.645 --> 09:08.949
YOU WILL ALWAYS
WORK A SYSTEM.

09:08.982 --> 09:10.951
I DON'T KNOW WHY.

09:10.984 --> 09:12.953
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU

09:12.986 --> 09:14.087
OR WHO MADE YOU THIS WAY.

09:14.121 --> 09:17.424
BUT I HOPE
YOU UNDERSTAND SOMEDAY

09:17.457 --> 09:21.728
EVERYTHING YOU LOST
BY LIVING THE WAY YOU DO.

09:21.762 --> 09:24.965
I'M VERY...

09:24.998 --> 09:28.101
DISAPPOINTED...

09:28.135 --> 09:30.337
I COULDN'T HELP YOU.

09:33.073 --> 09:35.876
YEAH, I DON'T NEED
YOUR HELP...

09:35.909 --> 09:37.211
OR YOUR JUDGMENT.

09:37.244 --> 09:39.379
I‐I'M FINE
WITH WHAT I'VE DONE,

09:39.413 --> 09:44.284
AND I'M NOT PRETENDING
TO BE ANYBODY ELSE.

09:46.119 --> 09:49.790
I KNOW WHO I AM.

09:49.823 --> 09:52.726
I'M GONNA GO CLEAR OUT
MY STUFF.

10:04.238 --> 10:06.740
SO, WHO ARE WE
STAKING OUT?

10:06.773 --> 10:08.208
RED PANTS.

10:08.242 --> 10:11.111
DRUG DEALER?
TEEN PIMP?

10:11.144 --> 10:13.447
I READ ABOUT A KID WHO WAS
RUNNING A PROSTITUTION RING

10:13.480 --> 10:15.449
OUT OF THE MOTEL
NEXT TO HIS HIGH SCHOOL.

10:15.482 --> 10:17.351
ALL THE HOOKERS WERE GIRLS
FROM HIS FRENCH CLASS,

10:17.384 --> 10:18.886
AND THE JOHNS
WERE THESE MIDDLE‐AGED GUYS ‐‐

10:18.919 --> 10:21.121
THAT'S MY STEPSON.

10:23.957 --> 10:26.793
HIS GRADUATION PRESENT.

10:26.827 --> 10:28.095
GO AND GIVE IT TO HIM.

10:28.128 --> 10:31.798
OH. OH. UM...SURE.

10:31.832 --> 10:33.100
SORRY.

10:34.001 --> 10:35.269
WAIT.

10:35.302 --> 10:38.639
TELL HIM HIS DAD
WANTS TO TALK TO HIM.

10:38.672 --> 10:43.877
NOT HIS BIOLOGICAL,
PIECE OF SHIT, FUCKHEAD DAD

10:43.911 --> 10:45.012
WHO BANGED
HIS MOTHER ONCE,

10:45.045 --> 10:46.880
THEN DISAPPEARED
FOR 14 YEARS

10:46.914 --> 10:49.183
TO FIND HIS FUCKING BLISS
IN BOCA RATON,

10:49.216 --> 10:50.817
BUT THE OTHER ONE...

10:50.851 --> 10:53.487
WHO TAUGHT HIM
HOW TO RIDE A BIKE

10:53.520 --> 10:55.422
WANTS TO TALK TO HIM.

10:55.455 --> 10:57.357
UM...OKAY.

10:57.391 --> 11:02.029
AND TELL HIM
HE'S GOT TO OPEN IT FIRST,

11:02.062 --> 11:04.298
AND THEN HE CAN COME
AND TALK TO ME.

11:04.331 --> 11:05.632
ALL RIGHT?

11:05.666 --> 11:07.901
OKAY. YEAH. SURE.

11:07.935 --> 11:10.070
UM...

11:10.103 --> 11:11.939
I‐I'M NOT GONNA SAY
THE OTHER STUFF.

11:11.972 --> 11:14.308
YEAH. THAT'S PROBABLY
A GOOD IDEA.

11:14.341 --> 11:16.743
OKAY.

11:22.883 --> 11:25.719
SHE PUT UP
NEW ONES TODAY?

11:25.752 --> 11:27.087
MM. OH, YEAH.

11:27.120 --> 11:30.157
I'M LOOKING AT THEM
RIGHT NOW.

11:30.190 --> 11:32.426
SHE ‐‐ SHE LOOKS TAN.

11:32.459 --> 11:35.095
YEAH, SHE'LL NEVER GET TAN
ENOUGH FOR HIM.

11:35.128 --> 11:36.964
DOWNLOAD THEM ALL
AND PUT THEM

11:36.997 --> 11:38.131
IN THE FILE MARKED
"BITCH EX‐WIFE."

11:38.165 --> 11:41.101
YOU SEE HIS YACHT,
THE <i>MISS DAISY?</i>

11:41.134 --> 11:42.703
OH, YEAH. IT'S BIG.

11:42.736 --> 11:45.806
WHO GOES ON A FISHING TRIP
WITH MORGAN FREEMAN ANYWAY?

11:45.839 --> 11:47.140
YOU THINK DANA'S
DOING THE OREO

11:47.174 --> 11:48.976
WITH BOTH OF THEM
BELOW DECK?

11:49.009 --> 11:50.844
YOU EVER DO THE OREO,
NANCE?

11:50.878 --> 11:53.113
I DID
A HALF‐OREO‐BANANA ONCE.

11:53.146 --> 11:56.917
I JUST DID 26 MINUTES ON MINE.
NEW RECORD.

11:56.950 --> 11:59.953
MY ABS ARE LIKE GRANITE.
HIT ME.

11:59.987 --> 12:01.622
GO AHEAD. HIT ME.

12:01.655 --> 12:04.057
I'M GONNA GO CHECK ON
WHIT.

12:04.091 --> 12:06.226
OKAY.
KEEP GOING ON THIS.

12:06.260 --> 12:08.762
DON'T LET THE TIMER STOP.
WILL DO.

12:08.795 --> 12:10.097
HEY, RICK.
CHECK OUT MY SIX‐PACK.

12:15.702 --> 12:17.070
WOW.

12:18.705 --> 12:20.207
THAT'S QUITE A HICKEY.

12:21.542 --> 12:23.010
LOOKS FRESH.

12:23.043 --> 12:25.879
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S A RASH.

12:25.913 --> 12:28.215
I REALLY SHOULDN'T
WEAR SYNTHETICS.

12:28.248 --> 12:31.218
I USED TO GET RASHES
LIKE THAT, TOO.

12:31.251 --> 12:33.520
BACK WHEN I WORE
SYNTHETICS.

12:33.554 --> 12:35.155
WHAT ARE YOU WORKING ON?

12:35.189 --> 12:36.223
UH, DO I KNOW YOU?

12:36.256 --> 12:39.760
FOSTER GRANT?
UM, CALVIN KLEIN?

12:39.793 --> 12:41.929
YOU CAN CALL ME
WHATEVER YOU LIKE.

12:41.962 --> 12:42.963
OH. OKAY.

12:42.996 --> 12:45.832
UM, THEN I'M GONNA
CALL YOU CHUCK.

12:45.866 --> 12:48.802
OKAY.
AND YOU SHALL BE...

12:48.836 --> 12:49.870
THIS HANDLE.

12:49.903 --> 12:53.707
HE'S ASKED ME TO FIX IT
FOR TWO WEEKS.

12:53.740 --> 12:58.111
I'M A BAD, BAD SECRETARY,
CHUCK.

13:06.720 --> 13:07.955
IT'S GOOD, YES?

13:07.988 --> 13:10.958
YEAH, NO.
NO, THIS IS CRAP.

13:10.991 --> 13:13.527
THESE ARE BACKUPS
OF THEIR BULLSHIT DOCUMENTS.

13:13.560 --> 13:15.996
I‐I NEED THE REAL SHIT ‐‐

13:16.029 --> 13:18.665
WHERE THE MONEY'S GOING,
HOW THE C. E. O. FILTERS IT,

13:18.699 --> 13:21.835
HOW MANY LEVELS DOWN IT GOES,
WHO KNOWS WHAT.

13:21.869 --> 13:23.237
[ SIGHS ]

13:23.270 --> 13:25.772
MOST IMPORTANTLY, I‐I'M CONFUSED
ABOUT YOUR HICKEYS,

13:25.806 --> 13:28.842
'CAUSE THEY SEEM TO BE OF TWO
VERY DIFFERENT MOUTH SIZES.

13:28.876 --> 13:31.411
THE LEFT IS SMALL, BUT THE ONE
ON THE RIGHT IS QUITE A BIT ‐‐

13:31.445 --> 13:32.913
YES. YEAH, OKAY.

13:32.946 --> 13:35.015
[ SIGHS ]

13:35.916 --> 13:37.751
LISTEN.

13:38.986 --> 13:40.487
WHOEVER TARGETED YOU
AS AN INFORMANT

13:40.521 --> 13:41.555
WAS ASLEEP AT THE WHEEL.

13:41.588 --> 13:44.391
IT'S NO SHOCK, GIVEN THE WAY
MY DEPARTMENT IS RUN.

13:44.424 --> 13:46.159
I'M SORRY YOU'LL BE GOING
BACK TO THAT HALFWAY HOUSE.

13:46.193 --> 13:48.829
OR MAYBE DIRECTLY
BACK TO PRISON.

13:48.862 --> 13:50.130
I‐I FORGET YOUR DETAILS.

13:50.163 --> 13:52.266
AT ANY RATE, YOUR SENTENCE
WASN'T THAT LONG, RIGHT?

13:52.299 --> 13:53.166
WHAT?

13:53.200 --> 13:54.668
WOMEN USUALLY MAKE FRIENDS
BEHIND BARS.

13:54.701 --> 13:56.370
THAT'S WHAT I READ.
IT SHOULDN'T BE TOO BAD.

13:56.403 --> 13:57.871
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?!
WHAT?

13:57.905 --> 14:01.408
I'M NOT GOING BACK TO PRISON,
THAT'S WHAT!

14:01.441 --> 14:03.944
I'LL GET YOU...

14:03.977 --> 14:06.113
ANYTHING YOU NEED.

14:06.146 --> 14:08.282
I'LL GO HIGHER ‐‐
C. E. O.

14:08.315 --> 14:10.617
W‐WHATEVER INFORMATION
YOU NEED ‐‐

14:10.651 --> 14:12.319
PERSONAL LIFE,
BANK ACCOUNTS.

14:12.352 --> 14:15.055
YOU HAVE ACCESS TO THE C. E. O.'s
BANK ACCOUNTS?

14:15.088 --> 14:17.891
[ SIGHS ]
MAYBE.

14:17.925 --> 14:19.893
WHERE DO YOU THINK
THIS CAME FROM?

14:19.927 --> 14:21.028
SO THE OTHER ONE?

14:21.061 --> 14:24.398
HE OPENED WIDER.

14:30.170 --> 14:32.706
HE SAID IT'S OKAY.

14:32.739 --> 14:33.907
WHAT'S OKAY?

14:33.941 --> 14:36.877
HE DOESN'T WANT IT
RIGHT NOW.

14:36.910 --> 14:38.979
SAID HE DIDN'T
WANT TO OFFEND ROY.

14:39.913 --> 14:43.116
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT IS?

14:44.184 --> 14:47.988
THAT'S MY DAD'S WATCH.

14:48.021 --> 14:51.158
HE GAVE IT TO ME
ON MY 18th BIRTHDAY.

14:57.698 --> 15:00.167
Y‐YOUR BREATH IS FINE.

15:05.472 --> 15:08.442
AHH.

15:08.475 --> 15:12.446
BUT MY SOUL IS
A FUCKING TRAIN WRECK.

15:12.479 --> 15:14.414
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

15:20.287 --> 15:21.755
Psst! Chuck.

15:23.123 --> 15:25.759
HEY, THERE, CHERRY PIE.

15:25.792 --> 15:28.962
[ CHUCKLES ] CHERRY PIE?
THAT'S GOOD. I LIKE THAT.

15:28.996 --> 15:30.264
HOW YOU DOING?

15:30.297 --> 15:34.268
UM, SO, IF CHERRY
COULD GET A PASS

15:34.301 --> 15:36.537
TO GO OUT TONIGHT,
WOULD CHUCK BE GAME?

15:36.570 --> 15:38.872
SURE.

15:38.906 --> 15:41.708
WHERE WOULD CHERRY
WANT TO GO?

15:41.742 --> 15:45.345
UM, SOMEWHERE
VERY EXPENSIVE...

15:45.379 --> 15:49.716
WITH, UM, ENDANGERED SPECIES
ON THE MENU.

15:49.750 --> 15:51.552
CHERRY WANTS
PANDA SOUP.

15:51.585 --> 15:55.589
AH. YOU KNOW WHAT?
CHUCK KNOWS JUST THE PLACE.

15:55.622 --> 15:57.491
OKAY.

15:57.524 --> 15:58.759
[ <i>DANCE MUSIC PLAYING</i>]

15:58.792 --> 16:02.129
THANKS FOR DOING THIS, MAN.
15% ON EVERY SALE, ALL RIGHT?

16:09.670 --> 16:11.805
HEY.

16:11.839 --> 16:12.940
WE HAVE ORDERS
WHEN YOU'RE DONE

16:12.973 --> 16:15.142
LAYING DOWN
THE FRESH BEATS.

16:18.212 --> 16:19.112
HI.

16:19.146 --> 16:20.280
I DON'T WORK HERE.

16:20.314 --> 16:22.349
YEAH, WELL, UH,
YOU DO, ACTUALLY.

16:23.350 --> 16:24.985
WE SAW YOU
IN THE STYLE SECTION ONLINE.

16:25.018 --> 16:26.320
IT'S A GREAT PHOTO
OF YOU.

16:26.353 --> 16:29.489
AGREED, AGREED.
SO, LISTEN.

16:29.523 --> 16:31.758
FROM ONE INDUSTRY PROFESSIONAL
TO ANOTHER,

16:31.792 --> 16:32.993
IT'S REALLY STUPID TO HAVE

16:33.026 --> 16:34.895
ALL YOUR MESSENGERS
RIDE THE SAME BIKE

16:34.928 --> 16:36.530
AND DRESS THE SAME,
TOO,

16:36.563 --> 16:38.799
THOUGH I DON'T THINK
THAT'S INTENTIONAL.

16:38.832 --> 16:40.200
WAIT, WHO ARE YOU?

16:40.234 --> 16:42.402
EMISSARIES.
FROM POUNCY HOUSE.

16:42.436 --> 16:45.272
WHAT?
POUNCY HOUSE
PARTY RENTALS.

16:45.305 --> 16:46.306
THAT'S US.

16:46.340 --> 16:48.809
WE SUPPLY EVERYTHING YOU NEED
FOR THE PARTY...

16:48.842 --> 16:50.110
EXCEPT
THE POUNCY HOUSE.

16:50.143 --> 16:53.647
UH, DO YOU MEAN
BOUNCY HOUSE?

16:53.680 --> 16:55.983
NO, WE POUNCE.
WE DON'T BOUNCE.

16:56.016 --> 16:57.985
SPECIALIZE
IN PARTY FAVORS.

16:58.018 --> 17:00.287
WE'RE THE BIG BOY ON THE BLOCK
WITH THE STICK.

17:00.320 --> 17:01.989
WE KNOW THAT
BEHIND THIS DOOR

17:02.022 --> 17:03.624
IS YOUR PROCESSING ROOM
AND CALL CENTER.

17:03.657 --> 17:05.993
WE KNOW WHO YOUR MESSENGERS ARE.
WE KNOW THEIR TERRITORIES.

17:06.026 --> 17:09.162
WE KNOW THEIR CLIENTS.
THEY USED TO BE OURS.

17:09.196 --> 17:11.732
AND THEY WILL BE AGAIN...
VERY SOON.

17:11.765 --> 17:13.267
IS THAT A THREAT?

17:13.300 --> 17:16.837
CONSIDER THIS A FRIENDLY
CEASE‐AND‐DESIST NOTICE.

17:16.870 --> 17:19.706
IT'S NOT GONNA BE
FRIENDLY NEXT TIME.

17:19.740 --> 17:21.942
PRICE YOU PAY
TO BE IN THIS GAME.

17:21.975 --> 17:24.611
I DON'T USUALLY GET
TO DO THE SHAKEDOWNS.

17:24.645 --> 17:26.713
IT'S VERY EXCITING.

17:26.747 --> 17:28.882
WE COOL?

17:28.916 --> 17:29.917
COOL.

17:29.950 --> 17:31.752
I'M DIGGING THE BEATS,
BY THE WAY.

17:31.785 --> 17:34.087
RETRO.

17:34.121 --> 17:36.156
YOU KNOW,
YOU LOOK LIKE THIS GUY

17:36.190 --> 17:39.826
I ONCE SAW ON A BILLBOARD
AT THE COPENHAGEN AIRPORT

17:39.860 --> 17:41.995
AT A STOPOVER ONCE.

17:42.029 --> 17:44.064
YOU COULD BE HIS COUSIN.
IT'S CRAZY.

17:47.467 --> 17:50.337
I'M EMMA.

17:54.975 --> 17:59.479
[ SIGHS ]

18:05.986 --> 18:07.154
[ SIGHS ]

18:07.187 --> 18:08.922
YOU DON'T HAVE A JACKET
OR SOMETHING, DO YOU?

18:08.956 --> 18:10.090
N‐NO.

18:10.123 --> 18:13.827
OH. MY FIRST
CROCHETING PROJECT.

18:13.861 --> 18:15.829
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:15.863 --> 18:17.998
IT'S ALPACA YARN.

18:18.031 --> 18:19.066
BE CAREFUL WITH IT.

18:19.099 --> 18:21.068
IT'S REALLY SOMETHING.

18:21.101 --> 18:23.704
THANK YOU...SO MUCH.

18:27.007 --> 18:28.408
QUESTIONS TO ASK HIM.

18:29.977 --> 18:31.778
GUESS IT'S TOO LATE
TO BACK OUT.

18:31.812 --> 18:33.180
I'D SAY SO.

18:34.515 --> 18:37.985
YOU HAVE NO IDEA

18:38.018 --> 18:39.253
THE FAVORS I HAD TO PULL
TO GET THIS TABLE.

18:39.286 --> 18:42.756
YOU KNOW, EVERYTHING
ON THE MENU HERE IS ILLEGAL.

18:42.789 --> 18:45.626
CURRIED MALABAR GROUPER
CROQUETTES.

18:45.659 --> 18:46.960
MM‐HMM.

18:46.994 --> 18:48.128
AND PUREED BLUE MOUNTAIN
WATER SKINK

18:48.161 --> 18:51.765
ON A BED OF MINT‐INFUSED
BASMATI RICE.

18:51.798 --> 18:53.267
OHH.
ENJOY.

18:53.300 --> 18:55.536
WOW.

18:56.837 --> 19:00.807
MMM.
VERY, UH...SKINKY.

19:00.841 --> 19:02.676
INTERESTING. VERY.

19:02.709 --> 19:06.113
YEAH.

19:06.146 --> 19:07.881
AH.

19:07.915 --> 19:12.219
SO, UH, HOW DID YOU START
VEHEMENT CAPITAL?

19:12.252 --> 19:16.390
WELL, NANCY,
I WAS THE CHILD IN HIGH SCHOOL

19:16.423 --> 19:18.025
WHO HAD
THE COMPUTER‐REPAIR BUSINESS.

19:18.058 --> 19:20.360
[ CHUCKLES ]
I ALSO HAD
A LAWN‐MOWING SERVICE.

19:20.394 --> 19:22.496
AND BEFORE THAT,
I DELIVERED NEWSPAPERS.

19:22.529 --> 19:24.932
IF YOU WANT THIS SHIT, IT'S
IN THE FAST COMPANY ARTICLE.

19:24.965 --> 19:25.966
JUST READ IT.

19:25.999 --> 19:28.702
NO, SO,
SAY AN INVESTOR WANTED ‐‐

19:28.735 --> 19:33.207
NO WORK TALK, PLEASE.

19:35.342 --> 19:36.376
BOYFRIEND?

19:36.410 --> 19:37.744
SYNTHETICS.

19:37.778 --> 19:41.048
[ LAUGHS ]

19:41.081 --> 19:43.650
I'M GLAD YOU
ASKED ME OUT.

19:43.684 --> 19:45.152
I DIDN'T ASK YOU OUT.

19:45.185 --> 19:47.855
OH, YES, YOU DID.

19:47.888 --> 19:50.023
I LIKE THAT
YOU'VE REWRITTEN HISTORY.

19:51.258 --> 19:55.896
WHY DON'T YOU REWRITE
THE NEXT TWO MINUTES

19:55.929 --> 19:58.365
SO THAT I'M DOING
SOMETHING MORE POETIC

19:58.398 --> 20:00.634
THAN GOING
TO THE LADIES' ROOM?

20:06.006 --> 20:08.208
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

20:15.082 --> 20:17.384
THERE I WAS,
IN THE BATHROOM,

20:17.417 --> 20:20.053
DOING MY HAIR,
WHEN ALL OF A SUDDEN, OH, NO!

20:21.355 --> 20:22.990
SO TERRIBLE.

20:23.023 --> 20:27.394
SO...CLUMSY.

20:27.427 --> 20:28.896
[ DOOR OPENS ]

20:28.929 --> 20:32.032
I KNEW THE MINUTE
I HEARD IT CUT OUT.

20:32.065 --> 20:34.201
I DIDN'T PUT IT ON
TIGHT ENOUGH.

20:34.234 --> 20:37.971
OH. HAPPENED BEFORE,
AND IT ENDED UP IN A TOILET.

20:38.005 --> 20:39.573
HE MADE ME PAY FOR IT.

20:39.606 --> 20:42.976
OHH.

20:44.678 --> 20:47.814
I AM SO SORRY. HE'S GONNA HAVE
MY HEAD ONE OF THESE DAYS.

20:47.848 --> 20:48.882
TURN AROUND.

20:48.916 --> 20:51.885
LIFT UP YOUR ARMS.

20:51.919 --> 20:53.687
MM.

20:55.589 --> 20:57.724
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

20:57.758 --> 20:59.459
FUCK THIS 30‐DAY CHIP.

21:01.028 --> 21:01.995
GIVE HIM TIME.

21:02.029 --> 21:02.963
WHO ‐‐ ASSWIPE?

21:02.996 --> 21:04.831
NO, BILLY.

21:04.865 --> 21:06.900
EVIDENTLY HE WANTS TO
BE CALLED WILL NOW.

21:06.934 --> 21:09.803
HOW DID HE SEEM?

21:09.837 --> 21:11.004
COOL.

21:11.038 --> 21:14.441
HE SAID TO TELL YOU
HE'S DOING THE 440 NOW.

21:14.474 --> 21:18.512
HE'S GONNA GET A SCHOLARSHIP
SOMEWHERE. HE'S REALLY GOOD.

21:19.847 --> 21:22.115
YOU WANT ANOTHER ONE?
NO, I'M OKAY.

21:22.149 --> 21:24.117
Man: YOU GOT IT.

21:24.151 --> 21:26.286
SO, WHAT'S YOUR OLD MAN
LIKE, BOTWIN?

21:26.320 --> 21:28.622
DEAD.

21:28.655 --> 21:30.791
OH, I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T KNOW.

21:30.824 --> 21:32.893
Y‐YOU GOT A STEPDAD,
OR...?

21:32.926 --> 21:36.230
TWO. ONE'S DEAD,
AND...ONE'S DEAD.

21:37.865 --> 21:40.133
JESUS. UH, Y‐YOUR MOM
A SERIAL KILLER, OR...

21:40.167 --> 21:43.737
MY DAD DIED OF A HEART ATTACK
WHEN THEY WERE OUT JOGGING.

21:43.770 --> 21:48.041
WELL, I‐I WOULDN'T HAVE MADE YOU
GO ONTO THE TRACK, THEN.

21:48.075 --> 21:51.979
LISTEN, IF WILL'S DAD
IS A FUCKHEAD ASSWIPE,

21:52.012 --> 21:55.015
HE'LL FIGURE IT OUT
SOON ENOUGH.

21:55.048 --> 21:57.017
JUST BE THERE
WHEN HE DOES...

21:57.050 --> 22:01.355
PREFERABLY NOT STINKING
OF BEER AND MOUTHWASH.

22:01.388 --> 22:05.092
POINT TAKEN,
O WISE LITTLE SHIT.

22:06.293 --> 22:07.961
BUT TELL ME
ABOUT YOUR STEPDADS.

22:07.995 --> 22:10.931
ONE WAS KILLED
BY ARMENIAN GANGSTERS,

22:10.964 --> 22:12.633
AND ONE WAS STABBED
IN PRISON.

22:12.666 --> 22:15.903
CHRIST, WHERE ‐‐ WHERE
THE FUCK YOU FROM, KID?

22:15.936 --> 22:18.605
THE SUBURBS.

22:21.141 --> 22:23.744
I WOULD INVITE YOU IN,
BUT, UH, MY KIDS ARE UP.

22:27.047 --> 22:29.983
YOU HAVE TO CLOSE
THE GATE...

22:30.017 --> 22:33.287
OH, RIGHT.
...OR THE ELEVATOR
WON'T MOVE.

22:33.320 --> 22:34.354
YEAH.

22:34.388 --> 22:36.390
TO PICK UP PEOPLE WHO MIGHT
BE WAITING FOR IT...

22:36.423 --> 22:37.724
DOWNSTAIRS.

22:37.758 --> 22:38.859
HI. EXCUSE ME.
HI.

22:38.892 --> 22:40.894
UH, SILAS, THIS IS ‐‐
YOU HAVE TO PRESS

22:40.928 --> 22:42.896
BOTH BUTTONS
AT THE SAME TIME.

22:42.930 --> 22:45.866
AHA.
GOOD NIGHT,
WHOEVER YOU ARE.

22:45.899 --> 22:47.868
NOT EVEN GONNA ASK.

22:47.901 --> 22:51.705
SO, TONIGHT,
UH, DENNY THE DRUG DEALER,

22:51.738 --> 22:53.574
WHOSE BUILDING
YOU STOLE,

22:53.607 --> 22:56.476
PAID ME A LITTLE VISIT
AT THE BIKE SHOP ‐‐

22:56.510 --> 22:59.880
CALLED IT A FRIENDLY
CEASE‐AND‐DESIST NOTICE.

22:59.913 --> 23:01.415
HE DIDN'T SEE
THE BACK ROOM, BUT ‐‐

23:01.448 --> 23:05.352
SILAS. WHOEVER I AM?
I'M FOSTER KLEIN.

23:05.385 --> 23:06.153
YEAH.

23:06.186 --> 23:07.988
YOUR MOTHER AND I
WORK TOGETHER.

23:08.021 --> 23:09.056
TOGETHER.

23:09.089 --> 23:11.859
YOU CAN
CALL ME "CHUCK."

23:11.892 --> 23:15.796
OH, HI. LOOK AT THIS.
YOUR DATE.

23:15.829 --> 23:16.997
ANDY, BROTHER‐IN‐LAW.
YOU ARE...

23:17.030 --> 23:18.398
FOSTER KLEIN.

23:18.432 --> 23:20.868
THEY WORK TOGETHER.
YOU CAN CALL HIM "CHUCK."

23:20.901 --> 23:22.135
CHUCK, PLEASURE. HEY.

23:22.169 --> 23:23.403
UM, YOUR FRIEND DEMETRI
STOPPED BY.

23:23.437 --> 23:27.074
HIM, I LIKE.
VERY COOL GUY. NO ISSUES.

23:27.107 --> 23:29.910
WE CAN TOTALLY COEXIST.

23:29.943 --> 23:32.546
SO, LISTEN.
MADE A DECISION.

23:32.579 --> 23:35.215
UH, DEMETRI AND I
HAVE BEEN TALKING ABOUT IT.

23:35.249 --> 23:37.518
HE AGREES.
HERE IT IS.

23:37.551 --> 23:41.688
NUMBER‐ONE SON IS REALLY PUTTING
A DAMPER ON MY LEGIT BIKE BIZ.

23:41.722 --> 23:45.192
I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN BEING THE COVER ANYMORE.

23:45.225 --> 23:46.894
SO I WANTED ‐‐
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU

23:46.927 --> 23:48.862
ABOUT SPLITTING OFF,
MAYBE.

23:48.896 --> 23:51.532
SILAS.

23:51.565 --> 23:52.933
DEMETRI.

23:52.966 --> 23:53.867
CHUCK.

23:53.901 --> 23:54.968
IS HE COOL?

23:55.002 --> 23:57.137
[ LAUGHS ]
OH, YEAH.

23:57.171 --> 23:59.006
NOT ASKING YOU.
[ ZIPPER OPENS ]

23:59.039 --> 24:02.576
YOU KNOW, IT'S BEEN
A LONG NIGHT, AND ‐‐

24:02.609 --> 24:03.844
BROUGHT YOU A PRESENT.

24:03.877 --> 24:06.747
WHOA.
MY KIND OF PRESENT.

24:06.780 --> 24:08.682
PRIDE OF
THE AFGHAN FIELDS.

24:08.715 --> 24:12.052
[ <i>INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING</i>]

24:13.954 --> 24:16.390
NANCE, TURN THAT DOWN.

24:16.423 --> 24:20.394
THAT IS
SOME REALLY HEALTHY BUD.

24:20.427 --> 24:24.431
SMELLS SUPER POTENT. HOW'D YOU
GET IT HERE ON THE SUBWAY?

24:24.464 --> 24:26.700
DRAKKAR NOIR. IT'S THE BEST
FOR MOVING PRODUCTS.

24:26.733 --> 24:27.701
POWERFUL STUFF.

24:27.734 --> 24:28.702
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S SAMPLE THE WARES.

24:28.735 --> 24:29.736
HERE, LOAD THIS GUY UP.

24:29.770 --> 24:32.306
YOU KNOW WHAT?
EVERYBODY, EVERYBODY.

24:32.339 --> 24:34.875
WE HAVE NEIGHBORS
THAT ARE PROBABLY SLEEPING.

24:34.908 --> 24:36.210
HOW MUCH YOU GONNA
SELL IT FOR,

24:36.243 --> 24:39.112
LIKE $150 A QUARTER,
OR...

24:40.480 --> 24:44.651
[ GROWLS ]

24:44.685 --> 24:48.822
HEY, CHUCK.
YOU SMOKE?

24:48.856 --> 24:50.891
SURE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:50.924 --> 24:53.994
ALL RIGHT,
SEEMS LIKE A GOOD TIME

24:54.027 --> 24:57.331
TO, UH, DISSIPATE THE TENSIONS
OF THE DAY, BOYS.

24:57.364 --> 24:58.832
[ LAUGHTER ]

24:58.866 --> 25:01.902
IT'S A GOOD TIME
FOR MANY THINGS.

25:01.935 --> 25:03.804
Andy:
UH, WHO IS THIS PERSON?
OH, MY GOD.

25:03.837 --> 25:05.138
SILAS!
[ LAUGHS ]

25:05.172 --> 25:08.976
I RECOGNIZE YOU
FROM THE PICTURES.

25:09.009 --> 25:10.844
OH!
[ COUGHING ]

25:10.878 --> 25:12.079
ANDY, YOU TOO.

25:12.112 --> 25:15.549
SUCH A PLEASURE TO FINALLY
MEET YOU IN PERSON.

25:15.582 --> 25:17.851
I'VE HEARD SO MUCH.

25:17.885 --> 25:21.121
WHERE'S SHANE?
NOT AT HOME?
MNH‐MNH.

25:21.154 --> 25:23.824
MY LITTLE BROTHER IS HERE,
OF COURSE.

25:23.857 --> 25:26.293
I KNEW
HE COULDN'T STAY AWAY.

25:26.326 --> 25:28.295
NANCITCHKA,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

25:28.328 --> 25:30.998
COME OUT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:31.031 --> 25:34.368
TELL THEM WHO I AM.

25:36.370 --> 25:38.805
SHE'S...

25:38.839 --> 25:40.974
[ CHUCKLES ]
SO SHY.

25:41.008 --> 25:43.810
NEW BUSINESS PARTNER.

25:43.844 --> 25:45.512
AND LOVE OF HER LIFE.

25:47.080 --> 25:50.551
ALTHOUGH I ALMOST
HAD REASON TO DOUBT THAT,

25:50.584 --> 25:53.654
SEEING THAT LITTLE KISS
DOWNSTAIRS, HMM?

25:53.687 --> 25:58.058
ANYWAY, I'M VERY EXCITED
ABOUT OUR NEW ENTERPRISE.

25:58.091 --> 26:02.029
IT'S NOT A DOG KENNEL
IN VERMONT, BUT IT'S A START.

26:02.062 --> 26:04.364
[ SIGHS ]

26:04.398 --> 26:07.935
I‐I'M SORRY.
YOU MIGHT WANT TO GO AWAY.

26:07.968 --> 26:10.938
BECAUSE I DON'T LIKE YOU,
AND I HAVE A BAD HABIT

26:10.971 --> 26:13.740
OF LOSING THINGS I DON'T LIKE
IN FIRES.

26:13.774 --> 26:15.142
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:19.179 --> 26:20.647
MM.

26:26.720 --> 26:28.856
[ SIGHS ]

26:28.889 --> 26:32.826
YOU HAVE HAD
A VERY TIRING DAY.

26:32.860 --> 26:35.529
SO GET SOME SLEEP.

26:40.901 --> 26:43.070
[ <i>Music continues</i>]

26:45.472 --> 26:48.675
